Author: beesocial
Title: [ANN[PRE-ICO LIVE]ðŸŒŸ-BEESOCIALS-ðŸŒŸ-ðŸŒŸGlobal Meetup and social events platformðŸŒŸ
Body: Here are some questions we have been asked:    1) Why do you think is there a need for a solution like this? simply put, what makes you think now is the right time, and why haven't others tried working on this so far? â€¢   There are millions of people organising and attending events on sites like meetup.com, around the world. Some events are free and some are paid. â€¢   We are also in touch with supper club organisers, who currently pay up to 20% or either advertise with Airbnb experiences for dinner parties or to sell tickets on Eventbrite. An example is the mensa supper club in London who is waiting to join beesocials platform. May other people organise suppr clubs in all major cities and have their own website etc but struggle to get the traffic. â€¢   This solution enables a network of local events, in local homes. If you move to a new city, you want to know your neighbours and the local area you live in, which may not be the city centre. These kind of social â€˜meetupsâ€™ where you meet likeminded people are usually in ity centre locations â€¢   Convenience and local: No expensive taxis fares, public transport, or long journeys in bad weather. â€¢   Cost: Drinks in bars are expensive. This is the reason house parties are popular with students. You can have the same drinks for a fraction of the price. â€¢   The platform will enable hosts to make more than 5x (Â£300) in one night compared to Airbnb (average Airbnb listing Â£60 in central London) â€¢   Others are trying it and we do have competition (Airbnb experiences, vizeat, meetup, verlocal )  Right time â€¢   Now if the right time, because the sharing economy is booming. The likes of AirBnB have paved the way for such businesses and this economy has grown exponentially in the last few years. Worth $15bn in its first 7 years and expected to be worth $335bn by 2025 â€¢   London is the best place for this because the UK is at the forefront of this economy, known as the sharing economy hub of Europe. Furthermore the UK government support it and have a Â£2000 extra tax free income allowance from the sharing economy   2) Can you share more concrete market data? Existing unorganized events happening on a time frame (daily / weekly / monthly), geographically? We have some data available on our whitepaper, based on meetup as a test case and also on food and drink in social settings. Whitepaper: http://ico.beesocials.com/BeeSocials_Whitepaper.pdf

Author: beesocial
Title: [ANN[PRE-ICO LIVE]ðŸŒŸ-BEESOCIALS-ðŸŒŸ-ðŸŒŸGlobal Meetup and social events platformðŸŒŸ
Body: Hello,  Thanks for your supportive feedback:)  The project is over a year in the making; We have laid all the ground work. We have an MVP/prototype(www.beesocials.com) we used for market validation for over 6 months. This was used to host events, generat ticketing etc. We have a number of hosts ready to board and potential partners too.  What people need to understand is, this isn't about some amazing innovation in tech that is the important part. This is about the wider business model, which will make people money! We have hosts who we have spoken to that will migrate over from AirBnB experiences because they charge 20% commission!   The web platform is expected Q1 2018. With mobile apps to follow in Q2.   People seem to jump on all of the cool sounding fintech, like brokerless financial tech, but We have a lot of experience in finance and investment banking within the team. Blockchain or no blockchain, fintech and epecially financial trading platform space is one of the most difficut to break into!  There are some large trading platforms who are already working on this kind of tech, like www.Murex.com  On the other hand, we have no direct competition:) So you tell us, who has the better chance of success?

Body: The â€˜AirBnBâ€™ of events; Use your space to safely host events to socialize and make money. The Worldâ€™s FIRST and ONLY platform of its kind,ANYWHERE!    CLICK HERE FOR BOUNTIES  Our pre-sale is now live with a 40% starting, but hurry, because it's for a limited time only!              The pre-sale will start on November 25th 2017. The pre-sale will last for a period of 4 weeks, ending on December 23rd 2017. The total supply of BEE coins will be 100,000,000 and no more will ever be minted.The exchange and bonus structure is defined below, with early investors being rewarded the most.      The ICO will begin on, January 6th 2018 and run for a period of 4 weeks, ending on February 3rd 2018.  We strongly advise, if you are interested in the project, you should invest early to receive the best price. After all, as the old saying goes, the profit is indeed made on the purchase and not the sale.  ...ICO BONUS ... First 7 days - 15 %  Reminder: If we do not meet our minimum target as detailed in the whitepaper, during the ICO, then these contributions will be returned to the wallet they were sent from, minus any gas.       In any business, of any kind, the people are the most important. We not only have experienced, talented and driven individuals in every one of our team members, but they are all passionate about the same cause, and they have been involved in similar start-up ventures in the social and events space. This is not merely a job for them, bringing people together and innovating the way we connect has been their passion long before BeeSocials. This also extends to our advisors, who share the same passions and have a directly relevant experience in the sharing economy (see team section).                  Why would anyone use your platform? Good question! We understand user acquisition will be pivotal to the success of BeeSocials, more so than the technology solution we provide. For this reason, we have an innovative and diverse plan to increase user adoption through multiple channels. This is largely incentive driven, both for hosts and guests, which provides a no brainer solution over the current options available, so it really isnâ€™t a hard sell. On top of the obvious monetary and convenience incentives, our user adoption strategies involve hosting our own BeeSocials events, partnerships with universities, hostels and hotels, as well as leveraging and adding to our large network of event hosts from sites such as meetup. We already have a number of hosts who are keen to start using the platform upon launch. Furthermore, a significant percentage of the crowdfunding contributions will be allocated to marketing, focussing on social media and working with a key number of influencers to reach out to our key demographics.  Why should I invest in BeeSocials over the other projects? We could tell you about how amazing and world changing our platform will be (which it will), but letâ€™s face it, any investor wantâ€™s to minimise risk and maximise returns right? Well, not only do we give you this option, we also give flexibility for multiple exit routes too! Short term investors can get their return on their contributions by selling their tokens on an exchange while medium term investors can take part in our voucher exchange programme and long term investors can hold their BEE tokens to watch the value increase and reap all the benefits of using them on the platform when they are integrated. Imagine if you had bought $100k+ of Uber credit, at a large discount 5 years ago?  What is the size of the market for BeeSocials? The sharing economy market is huge but not only that; it is growing faster than Facebook, Google and Yahoo combined, valued at $15 billion in its first 7 years compared to the combined growth of Facebook, Google and Yahoo of $11 billion. The UK is cited as being the centre of the sharing economy, being viewed very favourably by the UK government who have setup a trade body(SEUK) to support and empower this sector and the UK market alone is worth Â£20 Billion+, just on meals and drinks consumed outside in social environments.  How confident are you that BeeSocials will succeed? In any business, of any kind, the people are the most important. We not only have experienced, talented and driven individuals in every one of our team members, but they are all passionate about the same cause, and they have been involved in similar start-up ventures in the social and events space. This is not merely a job for them, bringing people together and innovating the way we connect has been their passion long before BeeSocials. This also extends to our advisors, who share the same passions and have a directly relevant experience in the sharing economy (see team section). To add to this, we already have an MVP, partnership with a large University and a number of guests ready to jump on the platform! We are very excited to say the least!
